name: Massachusetts mosquito virus
summary: Several Massachusetts communities are facing a high risk of mosquito-borne viruses, including Eastern Equine Encephalitis (EEE) and West Nile virus. Residents in these areas are being urged to take precautions, such as wearing insect repellent, covering exposed skin, and avoiding outdoor activities at dusk and dawn when mosquitoes are most active. Some towns have even implemented night-time curfews to limit exposure to the virus. The rare EEE virus can cause severe illness and even death, particularly in older adults and children. The virus is spread by the bite of an infected mosquito, and there is no specific treatment or vaccine available.
